<fig id="materials-12-00700-f002" orientation="portrait" position="float">
 <label>Figure 2</label>
 <caption>
  <p>The direction of the applied stress 
   <inline-formula>
    <math id="mm201">
     <mrow>
      <mover accent="true">
       <mi mathvariant="bold">n</mi>
       <mo stretchy="false">→</mo>
      </mover>
     </mrow>
    </math>
   </inline-formula> as a function of polar and azimuthal angles 
   <inline-formula>
    <math id="mm202">
     <mrow>
      <mrow>
       <mi>θ</mi>
       <mo>,</mo>
       <mi>φ</mi>
      </mrow>
     </mrow>
    </math>
   </inline-formula>, and the direction in which the Poisson’s ratio is measured 
   <inline-formula>
    <math id="mm203">
     <mrow>
      <mover accent="true">
       <mi mathvariant="bold">m</mi>
       <mo stretchy="false">→</mo>
      </mover>
     </mrow>
    </math>
   </inline-formula> as a function of 
   <inline-formula>
    <math id="mm204">
     <mrow>
      <mi>α</mi>
     </mrow>
    </math>
   </inline-formula>-angle lying in the plane (presented in the form of a green disc) spanned by the vectors 
   <inline-formula>
    <math id="mm205">
     <mrow>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mn>1</mn>
       </msub>
       <mo>=</mo>
       <mover accent="true">
        <mi mathvariant="bold">n</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">→</mo>
       </mover>
       <mo>×</mo>
       <mover accent="true">
        <mi mathvariant="bold">z</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">→</mo>
       </mover>
      </mrow>
     </mrow>
    </math>
   </inline-formula> and 
   <inline-formula>
    <math id="mm206">
     <mrow>
      <mrow>
       <msub>
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mn>2</mn>
       </msub>
       <mo>=</mo>
       <mover accent="true">
        <mi mathvariant="bold">n</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">→</mo>
       </mover>
       <mo>×</mo>
       <msub>
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mn>1</mn>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </mrow>
    </math>
   </inline-formula>. All vectors are unit vectors.
  </p>
